Key Match Events: Quinton de Kock and Rassie van der Dussen scored centuries, setting up a 200-run stand.
David Miller scored 53 off 30 balls, contributing significantly to South Africa's total.
Post-Match Reflections: South Africa captain Temba Bavuma described the performance as 'clinical.'
Rassie van der Dussen expressed satisfaction with the team's performance, saying they almost reached 360.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Keshav Maharaj took four wickets, Marco Jansen took three, and Gerald Coetzee took two.
New Zealand lost the bowling services of Matt Henry due to a right hamstring problem.
Neesham was struck on the hand while batting and was able to continue but struggled.
